OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F379A1778425867
OL,3,CLocal elections Midlands: What next?
OL,5,FBut elsewhere Labour bucked the trend
OL,6,Fand held on defying the Reform threat
OL,7,F- they are still the biggest party in
OL,8,FRedditch and in Tamworth - and in
OL,9,FRugby, Reform only managed to secure
OL,10,Fthree council seats.
OL,12,FOne remarkable change in these
OL,13,Felections has been the big jump in
OL,14,Fturnout. In Dudley, for example, as
OL,15,Fhigh as 50% in some wards - the normal
OL,16,Frate can be as low as 30%.
OL,18,FSo does this suggest a higher interest
OL,19,Fin which party wins? Or is simply a
OL,20,Fdetermination to send out a message
OL,21,Fthat voters need and want to be heard?
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G3/4
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
